##Survivors in Wuhan: hiding from disease, calculating the future

There are a lot of questions that we don't have answers to right now.

Foreword

It was a war that broke out at the beginning of the new year around every ordinary, ordinary Chinese.
This is our war. We discuss it eagerly, analyze it carefully, deplore the loss of life in the disaster, are moved by the fearless spirit of the healer, and work tirelessly for the little things we can do.
The Sea of life, we walk and cherish.
Netease's "Our war" feature tells the story of how, every day, we meet the epidemic shirtless.

Our War | serialized 09

On New Year's Eve, January 24, Kobayashi, who works at a local training school in Wuhan, waited nervously, the school's announcement: "The school will launch a web-based teaching system, and the remaining winter vacation classes and the following spring classes will be completed online. Please complete the preparation work as soon as possible. "
The result did not surprise her much.
Four days ago, the Education Department issued an emergency notice to all educational institutions to suspend classes. Kobayashi suspended half of the classes. A few days before the suspension, parents had asked the teachers whether they would suspend classes, and she could only respond with a slightly awkward "It depends on the school district's unified arrangements. " Then she encouraged parents to "stick it out for a few more days. " "years ago the class, only one or two hours left. ".
Student Oumi's mother, Annie, sought out the teacher, Zhou, to give her son the day off. Kobayashi and Zhou also advised her to "do not suspend classes, " because the system is continuous, if the children break, and then come back easy to keep up.
Annie nodded in agreement, but said anxiously, "that new pneumonia looks pretty bad now, " and then insisted on taking time off for his son.
Zhou posted pictures in the group every day, telling parents that the school was fumigating and ventilating every day, and checking the children's temperature before they entered the classroom. Children with abnormal temperature were not allowed to enter the classroom. With this reassurance, most parents settled down, rarely giving their children time off -- in Florida, less than 10 days later, the reality was so overwhelming that teachers feared it.
When Kobayashi asked Annie, a little uneasily, if he had ever blamed the teachers for not suspending classes, Annie smiled and said, "I don't blame you. Nobody expected this. "

The school, which is well known in Wuhan, has long focused on face-to-face classes.
Kobayashi is with the fourth grade, is the stage of gradually tight academic, most parents secretly hold back, think their children can be in the holiday "sprint" , the realization of the joke "curve overtaking.
Kobayashi, who has no experience teaching online, was at a loss, but at this point, she had to jump on the bandwagon, as the school eagerly purchased access to a piece of distance education software, called, organizing the school's IT department to prepare for what could become a cyber nightmare -- a prospect that worried Kobayashi and her colleagues, from the effectiveness of online lessons to parental feedback.
For the training of teachers, in addition to the professional ethics as a teacher, the recognition of students and parents is also closely related to the work performance and teaching rating, which is all the teachers most valued.
But Kobayashi is not ready for that yet. What she needs to do is set herself up as a school -- a stage that allows teachers to use their own devices to go live to Harvard, where her parents now live, the laptop he brought with him was unable to connect to his home network, so he had to contact his carrier in an emergency to maximize his phone's data plan and prepare to use the hotspot to solve the problem.
My colleague Zhang was confronted with a more difficult problem. Her computer just broke down a few days ago. This girl from other places didn't leave Wuhan when the city was closed. She was alone in the rental room for 3 days, tossing about for a long time, after remote instruction from several computer experts, the system is still inaccessible. She gritted her teeth, took all the precautions she thought she could, and went out, ready to walk 40 minutes to a college classmate's House to borrow an old computer.
"I never thought I'd risk my life to go so far for a computer, " she said.

After a week of in-house testing and testing, parents were notified on January 31st of the start of online classes.
From the moment the message went out, teacher Zhou's mobile phone became a hot line. Parents' messages are flooding in: Some are worried about a sudden shift in the way children are taught, some are worried about the effectiveness of online classes, some are asking, "how can we teach without the textbooks? " Others are outspoken, "What about the tuition fees? "
Zhou teacher answered the throat smoke, is the heart fickleness, anxious head rotten forehead, the son cried loudly.
On this day, she had no time to take care of her son from the get up, at this moment how the son refused to do homework, but also quarreled with her husband, teacher Zhou put down the phone like a member of the fire-fighting team to calm the quarrel.
Unlike many of the other parents'questions, Annie's appeal was simple: given the effectiveness of the online classes and the children's eyesight problems, Oumi will not attend the online classes for the time being, as for those missed classes, she told Zhou, in the future, it will be refund, delay or make-up classes until the end of the epidemic.
Zhou was relieved. Although she didn't know how the school would deal with such a student, it was a matter of the future. At least for now, the communication was easy for her.
"Okay, we'll give the parents a plan after the outbreak, " she quickly replied, with a polite thank you and a note to Ms. Annie to be safe and take care.
After 10 pm, the messages on the phone and wechat gradually stopped, and Zhou opened the dialogue with her best friend, Cao, as if they had been chatting for a while, also suspended at 9:30 in the morning after teacher Zhou received a call from a parent.
Miss Cao, a former colleague of Miss Zhou's, left the school to set up her own business and set up a small private "training excellence" organization after her lectures were sought after by many parents. Now, Ms. Cao, who is unable to teach online, is at a loss. She worries not only about her income during the suspension, but also about parents who won't stop when she can't teach, maybe move on to some other place where they can teach online.
"I regret leaving, " Cao said.

After taking time off from work for his son, Annie felt a little relieved, but only a little. In her view, remedial classes are a small thing, her son's school is about to start the course of online teaching, it is more upset her.
On January 28th, in her class of parents, the son's head teacher issued a notice: "The education bureau has officially issued a notice, starting February 10, primary and secondary schools began to implement online teaching, please prepare well in advance, to meet a different new semester. "
"It looks like it's going to be a long fight, " Annie said, glancing at the notice. The parents in the group were unusually quiet, Annie thought to himself. The details of the arrangement were so vague that they probably didn't even know where to start.
With that in mind, Annie and Chichi's mother had a private conversation. Chichi was a sweet girl, a good friend of her son's. Unlike Oumi, who had no heart or lungs and whose grades fluctuated, Chichi's grades were consistently in the top three of his class, making Annie envious of Chichi's mother.
Chichi's family had returned to their hometown before the city was shut down, and they wouldn't be back for a while. The Wi fi in her old house was spotty, and Chichi worried that if the signal was bad and the class was spotty, even if her daughter was well behaved, her grades would suffer.
It's not just the Wi fi signal that's driving parents crazy, it's the rush to set up a live streaming platform for online classes, as Harvard's Annie puts it, can you afford to have so many primary school students'computers online at the same time?
Annie Jokes about Chichi's mom: "The overachiever mom still doesn't understand my heart. "
Annie's biggest concern is the effectiveness of online teaching. Oumi was no stranger to online classes, but for a boy who couldn't sit still in class, most of the attention was focused on grabbing gold coins and sending flowers to teachers.
Several Times, Annie decided to give his son to stop the network class type tutorial, leaving only a foreign teacher oral class, as a dessert after dinner.
That's why she took a leave of absence from her son's Cram School, but if the school's curriculum is all online, she can't just sit on a stool while he's in class?
Annie and Chichi's mother became increasingly worried, and there were many questions they couldn't answer: If the school was teaching online and the parents had to go back to work in Wuhan, how could they trust to leave a 10 year old alone at home? Distance Learning, how can teachers according to the children's grasp of the content of the course to adjust the pace of teaching? The new term of textbooks, workbooks are not issued, parents can not go out to buy now, let the children only rely on electronic courseware, learning will be affected? Also, how do I submit my homework for Chinese class? Marking is also a problem..
The two of them put their heads together and didn't get much out of each other. The group also began to have parents ask similar questions, in the past, there is no answer to the head teacher, has not responded. Chichi's mother smiled and said, "maybe the teacher doesn't know any more than we do now. "

Annie also worried about his son's eyes. Over the summer, Oumi was diagnosed with 75 degrees of Myopia, and Annie, knowing better, gave Oumi a Orthokeratology. Two tiny pieces of plastic, like contact lenses, cost more than $10,000.
The doctor tells, the child myopic degree increases every 50 degrees above, must replace new Lens. Annie Bared his teeth in pain, but he waved his hands in deference to the child's eyesight.
Annie figures that if he were to spend at least six hours a day in front of a computer screen, at least five days a week, during 24 hour computer distance learning, Oumi's nearsightedness would surely increase within a month, if nothing else, there might be a bunch of other kids in the class with glasses.
"better than nothing, " Annie Thought, as she rummaged through the long-unused projector, consoling herself.

While Annie Fretted about her son's troubles to her husband, Zhang Wei, he seemed distracted. It wasn't until Annie lost his temper that he came to his senses.
But his wife's troubles seemed to Zhang like child's play. He worries more directly now, as if there was no money left. Annie was shocked to hear her husband say that.
She didn't worry much about her family's finances, but she managed to figure it out:
They had no experience buying insurance at first and didn't know how to spread their time. Several policies were all signed between February and March. At this time of the year, they had to pay four life and one car insurance premiums at the same time, totaling ten thousand yuan
The monthly 15 is the mortgage repayment day, to have nearly 8000 yuan of expenditure;
Her son's spring classes are due soon, and although she is currently on leave, it is expected that the school will continue to charge fees until the fourth grade, in any case, after the outbreak, the course will continue in Florida, just to keep the "small class" quota, also want 5 figures;
And the Lunar New Year red envelopes to honor both parents..
As Annie frowns and taps her calculator, Zhang Wei Leans in to remind her that the 10th is the day she pays off her credit card, and that her last bill was nearly 20,000 yuan. Annie's face broke into tears.
"The year is hard. " This time of year is the most difficult time for the couple. However, the good news is that each of them receives a year-end bonus at the end of each year, although the bonus is often delayed by the company until the end of February to be paid into the account, but put it together, and you can always.
Zhang Wei reminded her, according to this year's situation, when the year-end bonus can be issued, or even can not be issued, may have to play a big question mark. Annie's mind quickly turned away from his son's nearsightedness and joined Zhang in worrying.
You can be late for your bonus, but not for the insurance, the mortgage, or the credit cards. Originally the couple are just wage earners, there is also a jokingly called "four-legged swallow gold beast" school-age children, monthly expenses, almost no money on hand.
Annie sighed. If not, we'll have to dip into the Family Emergency Fund.

As Annie recounts, under current policy, Hubei regional enterprises are not allowed to return to work earlier than February 13, but neither their husbands nor themselves know when they will be able to do so. Like the jokes circulating on the Internet, you may wake up and have your vacation extended.
He is in a business unit with a limited minimum wage and his main source of income is a performance bonus, which can be discounted if he gives only minimum wage instead of going to work. But the risks of forcing her to go to work before the epidemic subsides are enormous, and the rest of the family has largely agreed on Annie's work: If, on February 14th, the company demands that she return to work without accommodation, prepare yourself for resignation -- Annie is in poor health, her work demands constant interaction with people, and her family is uneasy about being forced to return to work.
Annie is not reconciled, she has been working in the present company for nearly six years, the work is familiar, leadership recognition, colleagues amity, still a satisfactory job. It would be a shame to resign, considering the situation, and not knowing when to find another ideal job.
Speaking of excitement, Annie felt a surge of impatience.
But as Zhang Wei said: "Work is important or life is important? " Turned around, Zhang Wei and strong cheer comfort her, said that this is only the last step in extreme circumstances, "perhaps the company will allow you to work from home.
Annie nodded, shook his head and turned to Zhang. "What about you? I wouldn't trust you to go out if the epidemic hadn't passed. "
Zhang Wei also shook his head noncommittally: "that we both do not go out, who goes to work to earn money? Alas, when the time comes to say. "
The future is uncertain, except that the mortgage is fixed.

Annie was flipping through her friends' network when she saw one of the tenants' dreams, an online post that went viral with the phrase "ask your landlord if you can rent-free" .
Dream rented Annie's old house has been more than two years, each other does not get along well, but still a peaceful and tacit understanding.
At first, Annie because of dissatisfaction with the old tenants perennial arrears of rent, terminated the lease, and then dream on the recommendation of the agency to find Annie. Annie Remembers the dream when we first met: BANGS, long hair, backpack, cute. She and colleagues together, a total of 3 girls, blinking eyes, sweet mouth, a smile, shouting "sister really good-looking. ". Annie smiled. "Are you trying to bargain? " They laughed back. "I just graduated. The salary is not high. Can the rent be cheaper? "
Meng Meng, who was in her early 20s and had worked for more than two years, now works for a small trading company, which was her first job after graduation. The company was close to the neighborhood where Annie's old house was, and where many of her colleagues lived.
Annie didn't want to rent to a roommate, but the three girls were gentle and polite, and she relented. Three rooms two hall house, Rent 3000 Yuan, dream and her colleagues to bear together. For more than two years, Mengmeng never missed a rent payment, and she rarely bothered Annie and Zhang Wei, unless there was something unsolvable about a broken air conditioner. Then she called Annie with an apology.
Annie would sometimes see their group of friends, the three little girls, cooking occasionally after work, putting out plates and pictures of their hair and asking for favors, and Annie would look at the pictures and clean up the room. She liked the little tenants in her heart, and had not raised the rent, and hoped to be able to deal with them steadily.
Maybe it was a joke, but Annie was a little embarrassed to see his dream friends. She made contact with her dream, in depression, as if she had never left the city before it was closed, alone in her house, terrified and worried about the rent that would follow.
The two girls who shared a room with dream have decided not to come to Wuhan after years, and it is not clear whether they will come back after the epidemic. If they do not come back, dream dream can not find a roommate in a short time, then, the monthly rent of 3,000 yuan is a great burden for her.
Dream do not know when to resume work after the year, when the income will be discounted, if the situation is really bad, "maybe we have to rent the kind of more than 1000 yuan a room of the old house. ".
The dream said very bleak: originally she now do this job, do not very happy, originally intended in the Spring Festival after the first naked quit and then change a favorite job. But now look, years after the job situation is expected to be very ugly, she began to rejoice in the Spring Festival before the impulse to resign, "the company does not fire me is lucky. ".
Dream dream of the company only about a dozen people, the performance is also general, the boss often said, "can feed you, already calculate very good" . Dream's salary is just over 5,000, minus the insurance, only 4,000, aside from the rent, Utilities and daily expenses, there is no free money every month, occasionally reward yourself to see a hot pot movie, is her greatest happiness. Of course, such happy moments are few and far between. Most of the time, when she comes home from work, she is exhausted and just wants to stay in bed and watch the show. She struggled many times to quit, overtime more, pay less, and can not learn a lot of things, this job "do not want. ".
But now is not the same, well-informed colleagues say, the boss has many days of worry can not sleep, if the current situation, the company really can not last much longer. When the colleague was working overtime with the boss the other day, vaguely heard the boss in with a lawyer friend consultation: "If the suspension of wages is not considered a violation of labor law? " "If the outbreak of layoffs need to pay compensation? "
The gossip quickly spread, and for a moment everyone was in danger. That night, Dream Insomnia, this was once considered by her "chicken ribs" of the work, suddenly become precious, she even thought, should not send a message to the boss, take the initiative to say no pay during the shutdown, "can keep the job first. ".
Annie thought about it, but didn't say what she was going to say: "Your boss isn't going to make it, and it's not just whether you get paid or not that's going to change. " "How can you live without a salary? "
Dream dream hesitated for a while, said: "I still have a little savings, do not go on to find my mother. The epidemic will pass, for two months should be no problem. "
The fact that Annie had never been asked to reduce his rent from start to finish made Annie feel bad. As a young woman, Annie had lived a similar life in other cities, and she knew how helpless she felt when she was in a tight spot, but she never offered her husband a rent cut, is already the Buddha of the river.
Annie was distraught. She had planned her life like a perfect machine. She liked the security of being safe. But she rarely thought about how one of the gears of the machine would fall apart when it suddenly snapped.
If you look at the memo, the next time a dream needs to pay rent is in mid March. "Wait, wait till then, or cut her some slack, it's not easy for a little girl to be out on her own, " Annie thought to himself.

As she talked about her boss's plight, Annie Thought of her friend Peng Tian, who was probably just as anxious now. Then, gave Peng Tian to make a phone call again.
Peng Tian is young, but very capable. Founded and operates two private kindergartens, although the scale is not as large as those private chain kindergartens, but in his careful management, well-received by the surrounding residents.
This time of year is usually Peng Tian's busiest time. On January 14, the kindergarten was closed as scheduled, and before Peng could breathe a sigh of relief, he was in a daze: check the water and power equipment in the kindergarten, count toys and teaching AIDS, books and materials, audio-visual equipment, kitchen appliances and medical equipment and other supplies, inventory damage and loss.
After handing over the responsibility of the first mature kindergarten to another shareholder, Peng has focused much of his energy on the new kindergarten, which opened just two years ago. The kindergarten in Hanyang's new district covers an area of 1,600 square meters and has 10 classes. Under Peng's management, the kindergarten has gone through an earlier period of climbing, and has finally reached a balance of income and expenditure,
He and busy, and the partnership of the two shareholders, they are divided into three ways, in addition to the inventory of the current operation of the two kindergartens, but also a lot of energy to prepare to start the next new park.
Filled with ambition, Peng loved the prospect of Busyness, and his plan seemed to be in full swing after the Spring Festival, as well as preparing for the arrival of supplies and disinfection of the park, the most important part of the recruitment work and the deployment of teaching. When the kindergartens start, construction on Xinyuan will begin.
All those plans came to an abrupt end on January 20th. Peng is most thankful that all the children in the kindergarten are safe.
In January, Peng was still worried about the flu that was sweeping through the city, in Florida. Since December of last year, elementary schools and kindergartens have been plagued with flu, often from one sick child to another. Classes have been suspended. Peng made the health and safety of the kindergarten a top priority, requiring daily disinfection and ventilation, as well as stricter body temperature measurements in the morning before the children entered the kindergarten.
In retrospect, he still felt a Pang of fear. He tried to recall the children who had been sick before the holidays, calling one by one to ask if they were okay. In the end, he did not rest assured, simply inform the teacher, to call all the children in the garden return visit, exhorted, if there is anything uncomfortable, must be the first time and contact them.

When Annie called, Peng was sitting at home. He'd watched all the shows he didn't normally have time to follow, but the numbers kept coming back and forth in his head:
Without the outbreak, the second kindergarten would have welcomed about 200 children, and at $10,000 per child per semester, that would have guaranteed a cash flow of about $2 million, will have to support the kindergarten for the next six months of various expenses and operating costs, the remaining part of the profits of their several shareholders. Cash flows are suddenly drying up, utilities may be put off by the closure of kindergartens, but rents and wages in Xinyuan are, at a rough estimate, as much as 200,000 forex a month, the net cost is about half a million a month.
More troubling is that many parents who have paid tuition fees in advance for the next semester are asking for refunds. For the sake of the kindergarten's credibility, Peng can not refuse and can only withdraw money from the already tight cash flow for refunds. In Xinyuan, which was due to start construction in March, rents have been paid and there is no telling how long it will run aground... the only thing that hasn't stopped is the interest on the bank loan.
Peng days and two shareholders frown, they are not "mine at home" people, but take advantage of the young spell a breath to do something. A month or two may be able to carry it, 3 months can also find ways to raise funds, after 4 months? The financial chain is on the verge of collapse, and I don't know when it will come to an end.
Peng's most heated argument with shareholders in the past two days has been over whether to pay employees during the shutdown:
Peng wondered if it would be possible to discuss with the teachers whether they could not pay salaries during the suspension period or just guarantee some basic living expenses, and then give some bonus as compensation when the epidemic has passed and they have recovered, "Let's get through this. ".
But another shareholder objected. Today's kindergarten teachers are young girls, and private kindergartens don't have the institutional appeal of public ones. Without pay, these girls are likely to quit their jobs. That way, even if the outbreak ends, it will be hard for them to reopen the park in the first place.
The three men were at a stalemate, unable to convince not only each other, but even themselves.
"just wait, " Annie told Pang. "The epidemic will pass one day, and then everything will be fine. "
"I'll try to hold out until then. "
What Pang did not tell Annie was that by the time the park reopened, he would likely face many known and unknown additional expenses:
After the outbreak, as a densely populated area of kindergarten, the sanitary rectification will be more stringent than other industries, then it will be necessary to invest a lot of money to optimize and transform the environment of the park;
Facing the loss of students, more preferential schemes are needed to attract new students
When Xinyuan starts, there is bound to be an increase in labour and material costs, with at least a 20 per cent increase in construction costs..
He tried to push it out of his head: "It's No use thinking about it now. Try to raise the money first and keep the operation going. "
Hang up the mobile phone, Peng Tian turned his head to look out of the window, trying to squeeze out a smile. Spring, he thought, would return to us what winter had taken from us?

Kobayashi is with the fourth grade, is the stage of gradually tight academic, most parents secretly hold back, think their children can be in the holiday "sprint" , the realization of the joke "curve overtaking.

Dream dream hesitated for a while, said: "I still have a little savings, do not go on to find my mother. The epidemic will pass, for two months should be no problem. "

The fact that Annie had never been asked to reduce his rent from start to finish made Annie feel bad. As a young woman, Annie had lived a similar life in other cities, and she knew how helpless she felt when she was in a tight spot, but she never offered her husband a rent cut, is already the Buddha of the river.

Annie was distraught. She had planned her life like a perfect machine. She liked the security of being safe. But she rarely thought about how one of the gears of the machine would fall apart when it suddenly snapped.

If you look at the memo, the next time a dream needs to pay rent is in mid March. "Wait, wait till then, or cut her some slack, it's not easy for a little girl to be out on her own, " Annie thought to himself.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As she talked about her boss's plight, Annie Thought of her friend Peng Tian, who was probably just as anxious now. Then, gave Peng Tian to make a phone call again.
Peng Tian is young, but very capable. Founded and operates two private kindergartens, although the scale is not as large as those private chain kindergartens, but in his careful management, well-received by the surrounding residents.
This time of year is usually Peng Tian's busiest time. On January 14, the kindergarten was closed as scheduled, and before Peng could breathe a sigh of relief, he was in a daze: check the water and power equipment in the kindergarten, count toys and teaching AIDS, books and materials, audio-visual equipment, kitchen appliances and medical equipment and other supplies, inventory damage and loss.
After handing over the responsibility of the first mature kindergarten to another shareholder, Peng has focused much of his energy on the new kindergarten, which opened just two years ago. The kindergarten in Hanyang's new district covers an area of 1,600 square meters and has 10 classes. Under Peng's management, the kindergarten has gone through an earlier period of climbing, and has finally reached a balance of income and expenditure,
He and busy, and the partnership of the two shareholders, they are divided into three ways, in addition to the inventory of the current operation of the two kindergartens, but also a lot of energy to prepare to start the next new park.
Filled with ambition, Peng loved the prospect of Busyness, and his plan seemed to be in full swing after the Spring Festival, as well as preparing for the arrival of supplies and disinfection of the park, the most important part of the recruitment work and the deployment of teaching. When the kindergartens start, construction on Xinyuan will begin.
All those plans came to an abrupt end on January 20th. Peng is most thankful that all the children in the kindergarten are safe.
In January, Peng was still worried about the flu that was sweeping through the city, in Florida. Since December of last year, elementary schools and kindergartens have been plagued with flu, often from one sick child to another. Classes have been suspended. Peng made the health and safety of the kindergarten a top priority, requiring daily disinfection and ventilation, as well as stricter body temperature measurements in the morning before the children entered the kindergarten.
In retrospect, he still felt a Pang of fear. He tried to recall the children who had been sick before the holidays, calling one by one to ask if they were okay. In the end, he did not rest assured, simply inform the teacher, to call all the children in the garden return visit, exhorted, if there is anything uncomfortable, must be the first time and contact them.

In the end, he did not rest assured, simply inform the teacher, to call all the children in the garden return visit, exhorted, if there is anything uncomfortable, must be the first time and contact them.

When Annie called, Peng was sitting at home. He'd watched all the shows he didn't normally have time to follow, but the numbers kept coming back and forth in his head:
Without the outbreak, the second kindergarten would have welcomed about 200 children, and at $10,000 per child per semester, that would have guaranteed a cash flow of about $2 million, will have to support the kindergarten for the next six months of various expenses and operating costs, the remaining part of the profits of their several shareholders. Cash flows are suddenly drying up, utilities may be put off by the closure of kindergartens, but rents and wages in Xinyuan are, at a rough estimate, as much as 200,000 forex a month, the net cost is about half a million a month.
More troubling is that many parents who have paid tuition fees in advance for the next semester are asking for refunds. For the sake of the kindergarten's credibility, Peng can not refuse and can only withdraw money from the already tight cash flow for refunds. In Xinyuan, which was due to start construction in March, rents have been paid and there is no telling how long it will run aground... the only thing that hasn't stopped is the interest on the bank loan.
Peng days and two shareholders frown, they are not "mine at home" people, but take advantage of the young spell a breath to do something. A month or two may be able to carry it, 3 months can also find ways to raise funds, after 4 months? The financial chain is on the verge of collapse, and I don't know when it will come to an end.
Peng's most heated argument with shareholders in the past two days has been over whether to pay employees during the shutdown:
Peng wondered if it would be possible to discuss with the teachers whether they could not pay salaries during the suspension period or just guarantee some basic living expenses, and then give some bonus as compensation when the epidemic has passed and they have recovered, "Let's get through this. ".
But another shareholder objected. Today's kindergarten teachers are young girls, and private kindergartens don't have the institutional appeal of public ones. Without pay, these girls are likely to quit their jobs. That way, even if the outbreak ends, it will be hard for them to reopen the park in the first place.
The three men were at a stalemate, unable to convince not only each other, but even themselves.
"just wait, " Annie told Pang. "The epidemic will pass one day, and then everything will be fine. "
"I'll try to hold out until then. "
What Pang did not tell Annie was that by the time the park reopened, he would likely face many known and unknown additional expenses:
After the outbreak, as a densely populated area of kindergarten, the sanitary rectification will be more stringent than other industries, then it will be necessary to invest a lot of money to optimize and transform the environment of the park;
Facing the loss of students, more preferential schemes are needed to attract new students
When Xinyuan starts, there is bound to be an increase in labour and material costs, with at least a 20 per cent increase in construction costs..
He tried to push it out of his head: "It's No use thinking about it now. Try to raise the money first and keep the operation going. "
Hang up the mobile phone, Peng Tian turned his head to look out of the window, trying to squeeze out a smile. Spring, he thought, would return to us what winter had taken from us?
